andpoint. They won't even be activated until they are combined in earth orbit. 3. The anti-nuc crowd keeps claiming that Project Prometheus will lead to military nukes in space--more nonsense. Prometheus is white project done by a civilian space agency,NASA. It's based on 40 year old technology(Project Rover,etc.) It's not a DOD super secret project! Finally, lets all remember President Kennedy's comments on May 25, 1961 when ,in addition to the Apollo program, he requested money for an expanded Rover nuclear rocket program. The President stated then, &quot;This project (Rover) gives promise of someday providing a means for even more exciting &amp; ambituous exploration of space, perhaps beyond the Moon, perhaps to the very end of the solar system.&quot; Lets go to Mars! Rick L. Sterling <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=marsastronaut1>Mars Astronaut1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/27/03 11:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm28.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/fry1.gif" align=absmiddle>  Project Prometheus &amp; Anti-Nuke Movement</span><hr size=1> Sven Knuth of the German Chapter of The Mars Society was kind enough to mention to me that many individuals may have died because of atmospheric H-Bomb Tests. This may be true but to equate an RTG accident to the megatons of nuclear radiation released during H-Bomb tests is ridiculous! The anti-nuke movement should stick to international actions to prevent the spread of nuclear weapons(which I support)&amp; forget the peaceful uses of nuclear energy such as nuclear rockets! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgco